text: The Hoa Binh tree frog (Rhacophorus hoabinhensis) is a frog. It lives in Vietnam. Scientists have seen it in exactly one place: Hang Kiaâ€“Pa Co Nature Reserve, 1350 meters above sea level. The adult male frog is 31.1-32.5 mm long from nose to rear end. The skin of the frog's back is gray-yellow in color with brown spots. The lower part of its head, neck, and belly are light in color. The upper parts of the back legs and lower side of the front legs are orange in color. ==References== Category:Frogs of Asia
title: Rhacophorus hoabinhensis
